Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re <PlayerName>$player</>. I’ve heard about you from my uncle, <NPCName>Joko</>… The carpenter.//<portrait=annoyed>Tall? Mustache? No?
Actually, I also just moved here last Winter, for work.
I see a lot of potential on this island, and I’m sure I’m not the only one.//I feel like we could build the town up.
Stay with me here! Close your eyes and imagine a lush community garden where people gather.//<portrait=normal>Gardening on a breezy Spring day.
I see a lot of potential on this island, and I’m sure I’m not the only one.//I feel like we could build the town up.
Stay with me here! Close your eyes and imagine a brand-new recycling center.//<portrait=normal>The dumpsters are empty, and people are actively recycling. That’s the dream.
I see a lot of potential on this island, and I’m sure I’m not the only one.//I feel like we could build the town up.
Stay with me here! Close your eyes and imagine a lush community garden where people are gardening.//<portrait=normal>Chatting with each other.
Reuse your cups when you can, will you?//It can start with us, then hopefully, others will pick it up.
Besides, what have you got to lose, am I right?
A lot to explore here, huh?
I spent my first month just hiking around the island.//<portrait=annoyed>I got lost a couple of times and ended up in the forest.//<portrait=concerned>It was weird.
I have to admit that before coming here, I was very closed-minded.//I didn’t want to believe anything that hadn’t been proved by science.
I’m still like that now to a certain degree.//<portrait=happy>But some things, like fairies… They’re not too far out there, are they?
A lot to explore here, huh?
I spent my first month just hiking around the island.//<portrait=annoyed>I got lost a couple of times and ended up in the forest.//<portrait=concerned>Weird.
How are you doing here so far, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Does it feel like home yet?
Coral Island has become my home away from home.//After studying the local ecosystem, I feel like I belong here.
You live on the large farm by the forest? No way!//<portrait=happy>Beautiful spot. I live next to the forest too.//<portrait=normal>At my Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> and Aunt <NPCName>Dinda’s</> house.
Umm… Sure. Come over any time!//<portrait=concerned>I’m rarely home, though.
It took me a whole year to get to know this island and its people.
Looking back, I probably should have gone out more.//<portrait=normal>That would’ve made the process faster.

Be careful in the forest. I was out there when I got caught in a storm.//<portrait=normal>And listen to this. While I was looking for shelter, I found a little cave, so I went in, right?//<portrait=surprised>I mean, anyone would have at that point.
Then I realized the cave was actually an old mine.//<portrait=concerned>I dug up a couple of diamonds while I was there.//<portrait=normal>Do you know about this?
The mine is in the very back of the forest, right across the river.
Umm… Yeah?
Is everything okay at the farm?
Oh… Errr… Great talk.
I’m embarrassed to admit I got lost the other day, trying to find my way back from the forest.
I needed to collect some specimens for work, but I lost track of time.//It got dark so quickly. I had no idea.
We’re working toward the same goal, to make Coral Island home.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, you and me. We both want the same thing.
I’m kinda feeling it now.//<portrait=normal>Coral Island is starting to feel like home.

Be careful in the forest. I was out there when I got caught in a storm.//<portrait=normal>And listen to this. While I was looking for shelter, I found a little cave, so I went in, right?//<portrait=surprised>I mean, anyone would have at that point.
Then I realized the cave was actually an old mine.//<portrait=concerned>I dug up a couple of diamonds while I was there.//<portrait=normal>Do you know about this?
The mine is in the very back of the forest, right across the river.
It took me a whole year to get to know this island and its people.
Looking back, I probably should have gone out more.//<portrait=normal>That would’ve made the process faster.
I like to spend my Saturdays here.//<portrait=happy>You do too, huh?
Maybe I should be more adventurous. I don’t know.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to rush it.//There’s still plenty of time to explore in the future, right?
The fellowship with <NPCName>Ling</> doesn’t feel like work at all.//<portrait=happy>I’m glad she accepted my application.
My whole life, I’ve always liked the ocean. I want to spend my time here taking care of it.
Kinda miss the lab.//<portrait=annoyed>Work is all I can think of on my day off… *sighs*
I like to spend my Saturdays here.//<portrait=happy>You do too, huh?
Maybe I should be more adventurous. I don’t know.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to rush it.//There’s still plenty of time to explore in the future, right?
Kinda miss the lab.//<portrait=annoyed>Work is all I can think of on my day off… *sighs*
Why am I here chilling when I could be in the lab finishing up reports?
My family runs a boat company over on Puny Island.//Dad still sails as much as he can.//Any chance he gets, basically.
He’s been taking me out on boats since I was in diapers.
I spent a lot of Summers on Coral Island. Not always on this side, though.//<portrait=normal>But I always used to spend my Summer breaks0 by the sea, just diving and chasing fish.
My point is I feel like I know them, you know?//<portrait=normal>The coral reefs, the fish. I grew up with these fish.//Swimming around this kelp.
I don’t want to see them die.//Someday, I want my kids to know what I knew and see what I saw.
Once my fellowship with <NPCName>Ling</> is complete, I hope I get hired here full time.//<portrait=happy>Fingers crossed!
It’s not easy to find a job in this economy, but it’s not just about a job, you see.//<portrait=normal>It’s about this particular job.
Coral Island has one of the most beautiful coral reefs, and I want to study it!//<portrait=normal>I’d love to spend my life doing what I can to protect it from rising sea temperatures.
I don’t know what to tell you, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But I don’t think there are such things as mermaids.

I’ve dived my whole life, and I’ve never seen a mermaid.//<portrait=normal>Also, I’ve read a lot about the ocean, and nothing ever mentioned the existence of mermaids.//I could easily be wrong, though. The world is full of unanswered mysteries.
Milk? Eek… None for me. I don’t know.//<portrait=normal>I guess it leaves a weird aftertaste.//<portrait=happy>Now, lodeh. That’s where the flavor is at.
Oh, can you really?//<portrait=happy>I’m impressed. I can’t make lodeh. It’s a bit too complicated for my cooking skills.
Merfolk?! Around Coral Island?
Interesting, indeed.
Oh, hey! Happy Saturday!
Drinking too much milk gives me a stomachache. And it has that weird aftertaste.
I never made the connection until I had a minor accident at a theme park…
Minor, <PlayerName>$player</>. It really was nothing. I’ve shared too much. Bye-bye, now.
Tomorrow is work as usual for me. Nope, nothing special planned that I remember.
Oh, umm… I won’t be going out tonight. I have to be at 100 percent tomorrow.
I didn’t want to be rude by calling <NPCName>Dr. Jiang</> Ling. But she asked me to. It felt really weird at first.
<NPCName>Ling</> said it sounded too formal for her, but she was more than happy to address me as Dr. Widjojo if I preferred.
I declined her offer and said we could keep the environment in the lab casual.
How do you think they came up with the name Coral Island?
Ouch. Appreciate your honesty, I guess.

Special.SourceString: I think it’s a lazy name. You see coral, you say “coral.”

Text.SourceString: I thought so too. So insightful!

Special.SourceString: It’s known for coral reefs, so the name is to preserve the legacy, I think.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Very meta. I never thought about it that way. I like it!//You have a great way of looking at things. I like that about you.

Special.SourceString: A group of faceless people comes to mind. They’re sitting around a circular table, debating it.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is work as usual for me. Nope, nothing special planned that I remember.
Oh, umm… I won’t be going out tonight. I have to be at 100 percent tomorrow.
I’m meeting a couple of friends at Fishensips this Friday. Nothing special, just to chat and play some pool, maybe.
You know, the usual stuff. You should come out! It’ll be fun.
Not sure if you’ve noticed, but there’s not one store on this island open seven days a week.
It’s a good thing in the era of twenty-four-seven convenience, I say. It teaches us patience.
Except for the clinic. They always have someone on call in case of emergency.
Silence doesn’t bother me. I’m used to being in a lab all day and night. In fact, I really can’t work well in a room full of people.
I don’t bring my work home. It would be way too messy. Besides, <NPCName>Archie</> can be pretty noisy. It’s just too hard for me to focus.
Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> makes sure I don’t skip any festivals, because he doesn’t want me to miss all the fun.
I oblige.
I don’t bring my work home. It would be way too messy. Besides, <NPCName>Archie</> can be pretty noisy. It’s just too hard for me to focus.
<NPCName>Ling</> said it sounded too formal for her, but she was more than happy to address me as Dr. Widjojo if I preferred.
I declined her offer and said we could keep the environment in the lab casual.
Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> is Dad’s brother. You’ve never met Dad, but they kind of look alike. I think I look like Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> a bit, no?
It’s my eyes, I think. We all have the same eyes. It’s in our genes.
Not sure if you’ve noticed, but there’s not one store on this island open seven days a week.
It’s a good thing in the era of twenty-four-seven convenience, I say. It teaches us patience.
Except for the clinic. They always have someone on call in case of emergency.
Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> is Dad’s brother. You’ve never met Dad, but they kind of look alike. I think I look like Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> a bit, no?
It’s my eyes, I think. We all have the same eyes. It’s in our genes.
The water’s starting to warm up.//<portrait=sad>But it’s still too cold for me.
I was helping Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> weed the crops.//Spring is <Italic>finally</> here, isn’t it?
Sakura trees normally only blossom for a two-week period… Two or three weeks, something like that.//It isn’t usually a whole-season thing, but it is here. Must be something special in the water.
The lake is beautiful in Spring. Pink petals everywhere. But I prefer to swim in the ocean.//I kind of like the salty water. Is that weird? Ha ha.
I’m so glad Winter’s over with.//<portrait=happy>I feel a lot better now…

The hot spring near our house is sometimes visited by wildlife, like monkeys.//Especially in the colder seasons, like now. But I read somewhere they go there to relax rather than keep warm.//Their thick coats keep them plenty warm.
We should be able to see seals chilling at the beach this time of year.//Some are shedding their old coats, and some are there to get away from predators.//That’s what I read online, anyway.
There’s nothing like going to the ocean on a hot Summer day.//Except for eating melon…
Now <Italic>this</> weather is meant for me, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Hot, humid, sun blazing down. Love it.
If you get too exhausted at the beach – sun does that to you – go to the Beach Shack to cool off and get some coconut water.
The beach in Summer brings back some childhood memories.//Eating corn on the cob at sunset was the best Summer treat, back in the day.
The water here stays warm in the evening…//It isn’t too cold to dive at night. In the Summer, though… I don’t know about any other season.
Coconuts are seasonal here, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>I noticed each season has a different kind. Summer is that um…macapuno coconut?//<portrait=concerned>Or is it coral tall coconut?
The only time I truly feel at home here is when Summer hits and the heat rises. I guess I’m just a tropical boy at heart!
It’s starting to get chilly. I hope it doesn’t get any colder than this.
One thing I like about Fall is the fresh mushrooms. You can make polenta with them, and nothing beats freshly harvested mushrooms!
I love the Harvest Festival. It’s a good example of just how close-knit this community is.//<portrait=concerned>But then there are the Beluga Bay farmers…

It’s mushroom season, all right! Going to the forest to forage anytime soon?//Me? Nope, I don’t think so. I’m scared I might get lost.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe if I can get my uncle to come with me…
Do you know where I can get some bamboo shoots in Fall?//I went looking for them around the hot spring. No luck.
I didn’t realize Winters here were so cold!
I don’t think I’ll ever get used to Winter.
I don’t understand how some people can go out in this weather wearing only two layers.
I tried diving the other day, and it was so cold! It was horrible!//How do you do it?
I try not to go into the water during Winter. It’s too cold.// For now, above-sea-level testing only.
It’s too cold, <PlayerName>$player</>. Too cold.
Are there really two more weeks of Winter? I don’t know if I can last through it.
The New Year’s Eve Festival is going to be right behind our house. So there’s no point in not going.//You wouldn’t be able to sleep or do anything anyway. It’ll be way too loud.
This island is famous, huh? I’ve been noticing a lot of new people moving here lately.//<portrait=concerned>There was me, then it was you, and now the Pufferfish Corp.
Good point. I did come here for work.//And so did Pufferfish.
My parents never asked too much of me.//Just to make sure I remember to share what I have with the community.
I know it isn’t for everybody, but that’s how I was brought up.//We need to take care of each other.
Have you met <NPCName>Nina</>?//We met at the beach and got to talking a bit.
Apparently, she lives in the abandoned villa on the beach and now only comes here for Summer.
Wow, that felt gossipy. Heh!
Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> tells me festivals are a great way to meet everybody, especially since I’m new around here.
The beach cleanup is on the 28th, right?//<portrait=concerned>Umm… I think.
Uh… My mistake. I think it’s on the 27th.//<portrait=normal>I got it mixed up with the one back on Puny Island.
<NPCName>Dr. Ling</> and I recycle all the trash collected during the beach cleanup.
We turn it into materials for the town to use to fix community buildings or broken pavement.
<NPCName>Nina</> is smart and humble. I feel like I could talk to her all day, and I usually have a hard time chatting with people.//<portrait=normal>But with her, it just flows, you know?
I’m blabbering again.
I need to crank up the heater tonight. It looks like it’s gonna be a heck of a night.
Don’t freeze at the farm, okay? Heh heh.
I don’t think I’m going to enter the cooking competition.
I’ll definitely come watch the contest, though, because Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> is entering!
The house smells wonderful lately because Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> has been busy testing recipes for the cooking competition.
I’ll go with the rest of the family to watch the contest, but I don’t think I’ll enter this year.
I can’t believe I’ve already been living here for a whole year.
They’re right. Time does fly when you’re having fun.
It’s my second year going to the Winter Fair.
It was so much fun last year. I definitely won’t miss it this year.
For some reason, I concentrate better during Winter. I think it might be the cold.//Or maybe it’s because of the quiet.
That said, I definitely blame the cold for waking me up early. Heh heh.
For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the rain when it’s raining.
Like the phenomenon is so surprising.
Eventually, I want to publish more articles or even a book about my findings.
One step at a time, though. Yeah.//<portrait=happy>Don’t get too excited yet!
I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the storm when it’s storming.
Like the phenomenon is so surprising.
Eventually, I want to publish more articles or even a book about my findings.
One step at a time, though. Yeah.//<portrait=happy>Don’t get too excited yet!
Oh, you’re still here. It’s a bit late, isn’t it?
Why are you still here? Umm…
Oh, you’re still here. It’s a bit late, isn’t it?
Why are you still here? Umm…
<NPCName>Dr. Jiang</> published a couple of books and a lot of scholarly articles about her research here.
I read them all and even used a couple as references for presentations back in school.//<portrait=normal>She finds fascinating subjects to cover.
It’s still snowing out, huh?//<portrait=sad>I should’ve worn a thicker jacket.
I hope you have extra blankets in the cabin, <PlayerName>$player</>.//This snow doesn’t look like it’s going to be slowing down anytime soon.
Keep warm, okay?
I’m very cold.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
<NPCName>Dr. Jiang</> published a couple of books and a lot of scholarly articles about her research here.
I read them all and even used a couple as references for presentations back in school.//She covers fascinating subjects.
Did I bum you out?//Maybe I should stop talking about work.
In the future, I want to publish more academic articles or even a book about my findings.
I have to remind myself it’s one step at a time.//<portrait=sad>I can’t rush it, or I might fail altogether.
There’s another scientist I’d like to do a fellowship under.//<portrait=concerned>But I don’t think he’s currently accepting applications.
He lives in Mount Yahara, not far from here. But you need to take a boat and then a bus across the desert to get there.
The wind is so cold today.//I can literally feel it in my bones.
Maybe I should go to the clinic and see if that’s normal.
I love to go snorkeling. How about you?
I work for <NPCName>Dr. Ling</> down at the lab. She’s a great boss!
No, she didn’t tell me to say that.
<NPCName>Luke</> runs Socket & Pan, Coral Island’s premier electronics shop. Stop in. Tell him I sent you!
Watching Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> and Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> in their workshop is amazing. They create so many things.
I really envy people who can work with their hands like that.
Have you seen the oil rigs around the island? The Pufferfish Corporation set them up.
Don’t let their propaganda fool you. If they start drilling, it’ll be a disaster for the nearby coral communities!
They need to be stopped before it’s too late.
<NPCName>Archie</> is Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> and Aunt <NPCName>Dinda’s</> son. I think he wants to be a vet one day.
Even with a PhD in marine biology, I had a really difficult time finding a job. I applied for so many!
I’ll be forever grateful to <NPCName>Ling</> for giving me the fellowship here on Coral Island.
I love eating fresh vegetables from Aunt <NPCName>Dinda’s</> garden.//She’s also an amazing cook.
Did you know a quarter of all marine species live in coral reefs? Amazing!
I like to think of myself as someone who can keep a level head. I hope others see me the same way.
I love rainy days, but I hate carrying an umbrella. I’d rather just get wet.
Have you tried the tacos at Fishensips? They’re delicious!//I guess it’s called Fishensips now. Back in the day, when I was a little kid, it was called the Local Tavern.
I don’t mind living with Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> and Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</>, but I don’t like the smell of sawdust.
I love my job! Working at the lab doesn’t even feel like work.
We have so many exciting projects going on in the lab! Stop by sometime, and I’ll show you around.
Pufferfish Corporation is really getting out of control. Have you seen their flyers? It’s sickening!
Hey, there! How’s the farm? Catch any good radishes lately?
I, uh…don’t know much about farming.
Corals aren’t actually plants. They’re animals!
Don’t feel bad if you didn’t know that. It’s a common misconception.
Did you know sea sponges are older than the dinosaurs? It’s true!
Everything in life is connected. The sea, the sun, the sand…
I love helping our local coral population. I like to think of myself as an underwater superhero!
But I don’t like telling people I think of myself like that.
Why did I tell you?
Have you met many people in town yet?
I have a hard time making new friends, myself. Maybe because I don’t like crowds…
My fellowship at the lab isn’t a permanent position. I hope <NPCName>Ling</> will hire me full time!
Some coral reefs are over five thousand years old!
Do I seem tired? I stayed up until three in the morning thinking about parrotfish.
I feel so lucky to have Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> and Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> here on the island. I don’t know what I’d do without them.
<NPCName>Ben</> has some great deals in his shop!
I know. I was surprised too.
I always work late hours, don’t I? Maybe I should spend more time with friends.
Come to think of it, maybe I should spend more time <Italic>making</> friends…
I saw <NPCName>Archie</> playing with Taco the other day. It was cute! They really seem to understand each other.
If the Pufferfish Corporation isn’t stopped soon, sea life around Coral Island is going to be in trouble.
I’m a scientist.
I know you know that. I just love saying it. I’m a scientist!
I have wide and varied interests. I like staghorn coral <Italic>and</> sea whip coral!
I should probably get out more.
It’s freezing outside! I’m glad it’s warm and cozy in my lab. I spend most of my time there anyway.
Like my mittens? Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> made them herself.
It’s so rare to have homemade clothing these days. She’s incredible!
It’s finally warm enough to go to the beach again!
It’s howling out there!
Another scorcher out there today.
Did you know rising water temperatures are bad for the coral? It’s true!//I hope we get a break from the heat soon.
What a beautiful day for a swim!
I still can’t believe I get to be a scientist on Coral Island and spend my time studying coral reefs.//I wouldn’t have imagined.
Hmm… Well, I could, actually. I did have ocean posters in my room, growing up.//So, never mind.
My aunt thinks you’re a great farmer. Now, that’s one heck of a compliment, since she’s a great gardener herself.//<portrait=happy>She also said you’re a very kind person. Heart of gold.
She isn’t the only one who thinks so, by the way. I feel the same way about you.
How do you think they came up with the name Coral Island?
Or rather, <Italic>who</> do you think started calling it Coral Island?
I remember my first Winter here as a resident. It was a good time.//It took me a while to get used to the area.//I still don’t think I fully know the forest area yet!
Having you moving onto Coral Island a month after I did was exciting.//<portrait=happy>I couldn’t wait to meet you. Made me feel like I had a friend to figure out Coral Island with together. Ha ha!
I did my thesis on the effects of ethical dilemmas on coral reefs and fish communities.//It took me quite a while to finish because the topic was unusual.
I published a book based on my research too.//<portrait=normal>I have a couple of copies in my room.
I think the library carries my book. But I’m not sure if it’s been unpacked yet.//<portrait=concerned>I know <NPCName>Millie</> is really busy sorting out books and donations.
Keep an eye out for my book, <PlayerName>$player</>! Read it if you have the time.//<portrait=normal>I’m more than happy to discuss it with you afterward.
Looking fancy, <PlayerName>$player</>. Heading out for a wild weekend?
I don’t think I’ve ever met anyone like you. Smart, brave. Oh gosh. What else?
Would it be silly if I walked past your farm just to catch a glimpse of you?
I don’t know. I just really…wanted to see you.

I plan to publish more books when I gather more data. Maybe something about Coral Island.//<portrait=sad>But I’m afraid my study will never be complete, ’cause everything on this island is connected. The ocean, the soil…
There’s so much to look into and research.//<portrait=normal>I hope we can use what we learn here and apply it all over the world. The importance of recycling, for instance.
You’re not one of those people who think scientists are nerds, are you?
Well, unless you’re into nerds. I actually don’t mind, then.

I know not dating anyone can look lonely at times, but to be honest, I’m not.//Even when I’m alone a lot, you see. At the lab, working late into the night. Or in the field. Sometimes, I go months without socializing.//<portrait=happy>But to tell you the truth, I feel perfectly fine.
I’m okay if I end up going through life without ever finding a companion.//I feel like I already have a pretty great family.
For me, it doesn’t really matter where we are. As long as I’m with you, I think we’ll have a good time.
I could just sit and listen to you all day. You’re intelligent, and the way you think about stuff is…um…very insightful.//<portrait=happy>I learn something new every time I see you.
My job is important to me, but not as important as family.//<portrait=normal>Family is always my first priority. I’d leave this island tomorrow if my parents needed me.
Yes, it sounds extreme.//But the thing about my parents is they know how much this job means to me, so if they <Italic>did</> ask that of me, something huge must’ve been behind it.
We’ve never met each other’s parents, huh, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=normal>Well… You know my uncle pretty well, though, so that counts.

My dad sails and fishes. Growing up, I loved going on early-morning trips with him.//<portrait=happy>I don’t want to do that full time, though. Don’t tell on me, but I get bored fishing pretty quickly.
This job, being a scientist, is perfect for me.//<portrait=normal>I’m always on a mission to find something new. Keeps me interested, you see.
I stopped coming here for Summers a long time ago, so I don’t blame anyone when they don’t remember me.//<portrait=happy>I barely remember them.
To be fair, I probably came here only a few times when I was little.//<portrait=normal>I only remember how happy I was exploring the sea, not anything else, particularly.
Wow, I never noticed your eyes before. They’re so…umm…warm.//<portrait=blushing>I could look at you all day.
Is it cool to say that? I’m not scaring you, am I?
I had this idea jobs would be lining up for me as soon as I got my doctorate.//<portrait=surprised>But gosh! That wasn’t the case at all. I was so young and naive.
I’m glad I got a job here. If I hadn’t, I’d probably be at a corporation somewhere, testing food or makeup or something, trying for years and years to get decent work experience.
Oh, nothing’s wrong with it.//It’s just not what I wanted to do when I started studying biology.
I wish I had my own place so I could invite you over for a chat. Or a meal.//Whatever you want to do.
You can come over to my place, of course.//<portrait=happy>I mean, everyone knows we’re close. Just less privacy, I guess.
If I weren’t at the lab right now, I’d be diving all the time. I’d like to build the coral reef nursery myself.//Just get the ball rolling.
Well, I don’t mean right this minute, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>I mean, if I weren’t working at the lab, I’d be out getting my hands dirty.

I don’t think I’ll ever visit the cavern. Not because it’s Summer, but being inside the cavern, that confined space so deep in the ground… It’s terrifying.//It’s different from being in the ocean. The ocean isn’t so confined.
I think I saw Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> slip a little sawdust into his tea this morning.//That’s weird, right? It’s not just me?
I’m still looking for a new place to live. Let me know if you hear of anything, okay?
